{"schema_id":"pm.auto_decisions.schema.v1","decision_id":"AD-TRACEABILITY-GATES-002","timestamp_utc":"2026-02-25T18:11:00Z","scope":"plans.progression_gates.traceability_layer","inputs_hash":"b41c07432b47481924a5912ba8774d8d7ffe5688fafc084b9a12c0397d601e78","decision":"add_gate_011_012_013_and_requirements_quality_schema_and_ambiguity_marker_format","rationale":"GATE-011 enforces full requirement-to-node-and-check coverage so every requirement ID is traceable to at least one plan node and one verification check; GATE-012 enforces quality verdict==PASS on the requirements_quality_report artifact and mandates UI escalation (BLOCKED-state promotion) whenever needs_user_clarification is non-empty, preventing silent acceptance of ambiguous requirements; GATE-013 enforces that no unresolved <!-- AMBIGUOUS: <id> <description> --> markers remain in any tracked document without a paired auto_decisions.jsonl entry that records the resolution, closing the loop between ambiguity discovery and authoritative decision; pm.requirements_quality_report.schema.v1 is the machine-verifiable JSON contract for quality gate artifacts produced by the requirements analysis phase, enabling deterministic gate evaluation without human re-reading; the HTML-comment marker format <!-- AMBIGUOUS: <id> <description> --> was chosen for cross-format compatibility because it is invisible in rendered Markdown, safely embeddable in JSON strings, and parseable by a single regex across all document types.","applied_to":["Plans/Progression_Gates.md","Plans/requirements_quality_report.schema.json","Plans/auto_decisions.jsonl","Plans/Spec_Lock.json"],"contract_refs":["SchemaID:pm.requirements_quality_report.schema.v1","SchemaID:pm.auto_decisions.schema.v1","PolicyRule:Decision_Policy.md#spec-lock-update-protocol","Gate:GATE-011","Gate:GATE-012","Gate:GATE-013","ContractName:Plans/Progression_Gates.md","ContractName:Plans/human-in-the-loop.md"]}
