{"schema_id":"pm.auto_decisions.schema.v1","decision_id":"dec-2026-02-27-document-packaging-policy-defaults-spec-lock-refresh","timestamp_utc":"2026-02-27T01:51:25Z","scope":"plans.document_packaging","inputs_hash":"16ccbb94b248fb71da5ffd1f7074794d0a7813d8a7d2708d85a1783e28d962aa","decision":"lock_document_set_packaging_defaults(max_bytes=262144,max_estimated_tokens=65536,token_estimate=char_count/4,fallback_chunk_lines=400,primary_split=h2_outside_fences,fallback_split=fixed_line_chunks,audit_count=3)_and_register_policy_in_spec_lock","rationale":"Document packaging needed deterministic, non-bypassable defaults for triggers, split behavior, naming, and three full audits. Locked defaults: max_bytes=262144, max_estimated_tokens=65536 with token estimate char_count/4, fallback_chunk_lines=400, primary split at Markdown h2 outside fences, fallback deterministic fixed line chunks, and audit_count=3. Spec Lock canonical hashes were refreshed for all changed SSOT files so GATE-002 stays deterministic and reproducible.","applied_to":["Plans/Document_Packaging_Policy.md","Plans/00-plans-index.md","Plans/Project_Output_Artifacts.md","Plans/chain-wizard-flexibility.md","Plans/interview-subagent-integration.md","Plans/orchestrator-subagent-integration.md","Plans/Executor_Protocol.md","Plans/Progression_Gates.md","Plans/Spec_Lock.json","Plans/auto_decisions.jsonl"],"contract_refs":["Gate:GATE-014","Gate:GATE-002","SchemaID:Spec_Lock.json#canonical_ssot_hashes","PolicyRule:Decision_Policy.md#spec-lock-update-protocol","ContractName:Plans/Document_Packaging_Policy.md"]}
{"schema_id":"pm.auto_decisions.schema.v1","decision_id":"dec-2026-02-27-docset-path-convention-and-pointer-stub","timestamp_utc":"2026-02-27T03:06:33Z","scope":"plans.document_packaging","inputs_hash":"1778e2daf232d7f018fbe66d93141f132b764071e67afcf730d71555e3d63632","decision":"lock_docset_path_convention(docset_path_suffix=.docset,pointer_stub_required=true,pointer_stub_fields=[docset_entrypoint,source_sha256,verify_command],canonical_truth=docset_when_present_else_file)","rationale":"Document Set on-disk path convention must be deterministic: when packaging triggers fire, the canonical form is a `.docset/` directory adjacent to the original file path, the original file becomes a derived pointer stub with fixed fields (entrypoint, source_sha256, verify_command), and verification must enforce pointer-stub/docset consistency. This prevents divergent implementations from inventing incompatible path layouts or omitting the pointer stub.","applied_to":["Plans/Document_Packaging_Policy.md","Plans/Project_Output_Artifacts.md","Plans/Progression_Gates.md","Plans/Spec_Lock.json","Plans/auto_decisions.jsonl"],"contract_refs":["Gate:GATE-002","Gate:GATE-014","ContractName:Plans/Document_Packaging_Policy.md#7","PolicyRule:Decision_Policy.md#spec-lock-update-protocol","SchemaID:Spec_Lock.json#canonical_ssot_hashes"]}
